column1: # global_summary: Here we provide depths to the Moho boundary in KEA20
column2: relative to a mean Earth radius of 6371 km.; These Moho depths result from an initial inversion of point constraints from teleseismic; receiver function and seismic reflection studies
column3: plus additional Moho perturbations from the; surface wave dispersion data inversion. The reference model Moho is taken from CRUST1.0.  ; For additional information please see the supplementary information of Witek et al. (2021).
